{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines the Promoter's responsibilities for securing contracts with music venues, but lacks clarity on financial risk allocation and potential liabilities in case of non-performance.",
  "operative_text": "Promoter to provide certain skills, expertise, experience and abilities developed as global leader in the music and entertainment business over two decades. The Promoter will consult and work with the Directors and Officers of VNUE concerning matters relating to business development and other matters deemed necessary to perform the Promotion Services.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on financial risk allocation for the Promoter's performance, particularly in case of non-performance. This could lead to significant financial risk for VNUE if the Promoter fails to deliver on its obligations.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Promoter", "VNUE"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "non-operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines the payment structure for services provided by VNUE to Promoter, including a fixed fee and equity compensation based on contract signings. It lacks clarity on how non-payment will be handled and what happens in case of promoter's insolvency.",
  "operative_text": "VNUE will compensate Promoter i) Two Thousand Five Hundred Dollars ($2,500.00) for each One (1) Year contract Promoter secures per venue and Five Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00) for each Two (2) Year contract Promoter secures per venue, with payment due to Promoter within Thirty (30) Days from the date on which each such contract is countersigned; and ii) through the issuance of VNUE common stock as set forth below, and for the purposes of Rule 144 such shares of stock shall be deemed to have fully earned by Promoter upon the date of each issuance of such stock certificates by VStock Transfer:   Three Million (3,000,000) shares of VNUE common stock shall be awarded to Promoter for performing Promotion Services as follows:\nFor every Five (5) music venues that sign a contract with VNUE, Six Hundred Thousand (600,000) shares of VNUE common stock shall be awarded to Promoter;   and If Ten (10) music venues sign a contract with VNUE before January 16, 2016, Promoter will receive an additional bonus of Three Hundred Thousand (300,000) shares of VNUE common stock.  Section",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on how non-payment will be handled and what happens in case of promoter's insolvency.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["VNUE", "Promoter"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines the reimbursement structure for expenses incurred by the Promoter, but lacks clarity on how non-payment will be handled and what recourse is available to VNUE in case of disputes.",
  "operative_text": "VNUE shall reimburse Promoter for expenses incurred by Promoter while performing the duties herein. Promoter shall deliver to VNUE an itemized accounting of expenses incurred on a weekly basis, and VNUE shall reimburse Promoter within Thirty (30) Days of receipt of such accounting.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on how non-payment will be handled by VNUE in case the Promoter fails to deliver an itemized accounting or if there are disputes regarding expenses. This could lead to significant financial risk for VNUE and potential delays in reimbursement.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["VNUE", "Promoter", "expenses"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "non-operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause addresses the non-operator's right to perform services and their obligation regarding trade secrets, but it lacks clarity on how these rights are defined and enforced in the context of a joint venture.",
  "operative_text": "Promoter affirms that Promoter is not restricted from providing services in this Agreement due to any agreement with any other person or entity. Promoter will not disclose to VNUE or use in its work any trade secrets, inventions or confidential information of any other person or entity which Promoter is not lawfully entitled to disclose or use.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on how the non-operator's right to perform services and their obligation regarding trade secrets are defined and enforced in the context of a joint venture. ",
      "severity": "minor",
      "references": ["Promoter", "VNUE", "trade secrets", "inventions", "confidential information"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause lacks clarity on how capital calls will be handled, what happens in case of non-payment, and how debt will be managed upon termination. This could lead to significant financial risk for both parties.",
  "operative_text": "5. Place of Work. Promoter may perform the Promotion Services at such locations as Promoter may choose.   Section\n",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on how capital calls will be handled, what happens in case of non-payment, and how debt will be managed upon termination.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["5. Place of Work"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause establishes a one-year term and outlines the possibility for renewal, but lacks details on how capital calls are handled or what happens in case of non-payment.",
  "operative_text": "This Agreement shall commence on September 10, 2015 and shall continue for One (1) Year (the \"Term\"). At any time prior to the end of the Term, the Parties may agree in writing to extend the Agreement for successive One (1) Year periods (the \"Renewal Terms\") under the same conditions set forth herein.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The agreement lacks clarity on how capital calls are handled and what happens in case of non-payment. This could lead to significant financial risk for both parties.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Term", "capital calls"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause establishes joint and several liability for the non-operator (VNUE) in case of any losses arising from the actions of the operator (Promoter). This could lead to significant financial risk for VNUE if Promoter's actions result in liabilities.",
  "operative_text": "The work to be performed under this Agreement will be performed entirely at Promoter’s risk, and Promoter assumes all responsibility for the condition of equipment and facilities used in the performance of this agreement. Promoter agrees to indemnify VNUE for any and all liability or loss arising in any way out of the actions of Promoter taken in the performance of this Agreement. VNUE agrees to indemnify and hold Promoter harmless for any and all liability or loss arising in any way out of the actions, during the term of this Agreement, of VNUE officers, directors, employees, agents or third parties not under the control of Promoter.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "VNUE is exposed to joint and several liability for losses arising from Promoter's actions. This could lead to significant financial risk if Promoter's actions result in liabilities.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Promoter", "VNUE"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause defines the scope of work for the joint venture partner (Promoter) and outlines their responsibilities, including disclosure requirements and limitations on sharing confidential information.",
  "operative_text": "All work will be done in a competent fashion in accordance with applicable standards of the profession. Promoter represents, warrants, and covenants the following:   A. Promoter will disclose to VNUE any and all material facts and circumstances, which may affect its ability to perform its undertaking herein.   B. Promoter is an independent contractor acting in the limited capacity as an independent contractor for VNUE.   C. Promoter will not disseminate or share with third parties any material information about VNUE not already contained in a Company report filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission, as Promoter acknowledges that such third parties might try to act on such material non-public information by engaging in \"insider trading\" to the detriment of VNUE.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "Promoter's responsibilities are defined but lack clarity on financial risk and liability for the joint venture. The clause does not address how capital calls, debt management, or potential non-payment will be handled in case of a default by the Promoter.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Promoter"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "non-operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause addresses the Promoter's legal right to enter into the agreement and indemnifies VNUE from any damages arising from a conflict with other agreements, potentially impacting the non-operator's rights and liabilities.",
  "operative_text": "Promoter covenants and warrants that Promoter has the unlimited legal right to enter into this Agreement and to perform in accordance with its terms without violating the rights of others or any applicable law and that he has not and shall not become a party to any other agreement of any kind which conflicts with this Agreement. Promoter shall indemnify and hold VNUE harmless from any and all damages, claims and expenses (including, but not limited to attorneys' fees and costs) arising out of or resulting from any claim that this Agreement violates any such other agreements. Breach of this Section shall operate to terminate this Agreement automatically without notice otherwise required by this Agreement.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "Promoter warrants unlimited legal right to enter into the agreement, potentially impacting the non-operator's rights and liabilities",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Promoter", "this Agreement"]
    },
    {
      "text": "Breach of this Section shall operate to terminate the Agreement automatically without notice otherwise required by this Agreement.",
      "severity": "critical",
      "references": ["Section", "this Agreement"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause defines how notices and communications will be delivered under the agreement. It lacks detail on specific notice requirements, which could lead to ambiguity and potential disputes.",
  "operative_text": "Any notice or communication permitted or required by this Agreement shall be deemed effective when personally delivered, or sent by certified or registered mail, properly addressed to VNUE or Promoter at the addresses set forth above.   Section",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "This clause lacks detail on specific notice requirements, which could lead to ambiguity and potential disputes.",
      "severity": "minor",
      "references": ["this Agreement"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause attempts to establish a complete and exclusive agreement, potentially limiting future negotiations on the subject matter. This could create legal challenges if unforeseen circumstances arise.",
  "operative_text": "It is agreed between the parties that there are no other agreements or understandings between them relating to the subject matter of this agreement. This agreement supersedes all prior agreements, oral or written, between the parties and is intended as a complete and exclusive statement of the agreement between the parties. If any provision in this Agreement is held by a court of competent jurisdiction to be invalid, void or unenforceable, the remaining provisions will continue in full force without being impaired or invalidated in any way.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "This clause attempts to establish a complete and exclusive agreement, potentially limiting future negotiations on the subject matter. This could create legal challenges if unforeseen circumstances arise.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["clause 11"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause clarifies that VNUE is not obligated to exclusively use BookingEntertainment.com as its promoter and allows for flexibility in contracting with other service providers.",
  "operative_text": "It is understood that VNUE does not agree to use BookingEntertainment.com exclusively as its Promoter, and that Promoter shall not be held liable for the actions of third parties which may also be providing the same or similar services during the term of this Agreement. Likewise, Promoter is free to contract for services to be performed for other public and private companies while under contract with VNUE, subject to the terms of this Agreement.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause states that VNUE is not obligated to exclusively use BookingEntertainment.com as its promoter. This could lead to a lack of clarity on the specific services and responsibilities of the Promoter.",
      "severity": "minor",
      "references": ["VNUE", "BookingEntertainment.com", "Promoter"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause addresses the governing law, jurisdiction, and liability for disputes arising from this agreement. It also outlines provisions for handling invalid or unenforceable clauses.",
  "operative_text": "This Agreement shall inure to the benefit of the parties hereto and their respective successors, heirs and assigns. In case any provision of this Agreement shall be invalid, illegal or unenforceable, the validity, legality and enforceability of the remaining provisions of the Agreement shall not in any way be affected or impaired thereby.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "This clause states that if a provision is invalid, illegal, or unenforceable, the rest of the agreement remains valid. This could lead to significant financial risk for the non-operator if they are unable to meet their obligations under the agreement.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["invalid", "illegal", "unenforceable"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

